{
  "info": {
    "name": "OTP Hora Backend API",
    "description": "Collection pour tester l'API OTP Hora (Express + Prisma).\n\n**Prérequis**\n- `base_url` : URL du serveur (ex. `http://localhost:3000`).\n- `api_key` : clé API entreprise (bcrypt). Pour la **première** entreprise, utiliser une clé issue d'un seed SQL / Prisma, puis `POST /enterprises` peut créer d'autres comptes avec cette clé.\n\n**Flux recommandé**\n1. Définir `api_key` (entreprise existante).\n2. Créer utilisateur → variable `user_id`.\n3. Créer lien `POST /links` → `link_id`.\n4. Créer demande auth → `auth_request_id`.\n5. Statut / événements / approve ou reject.\n\n**Note** : `GET /links` n'est pas implémenté dans le backend actuel (réponse 404 attendue).",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_postman_id": "otp-hora-backend-v1"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url", "value": "http://localhost:3000" },
    { "key": "api_key", "value": "" },
    { "key": "user_id", "value": "" },
    { "key": "contact_id", "value": "" },
    { "key": "device_id", "value": "" },
    { "key": "enterprise_id", "value": "" },
    { "key": "link_id", "value": "" },
    { "key": "auth_request_id", "value": "" },
    { "key": "recovery_id", "value": "" },
    { "key": "external_ref", "value": "ext-user-001" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET Health",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{base_url}}/health",
            "description": "Vérifie que l'API répond (réponse texte brut, pas JSON)."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "pm.test('Body contains running', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.text()).to.include('running');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "enterprise_accounts",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST Create enterprise",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "x-api-key", "value": "{{api_key}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"nom_entreprise\": \"Demo Enterprise\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{base_url}}/enterprises",
            "description": "Crée un compte entreprise. **Requiert déjà une `api_key` valide** (bootstrap via seed). Réponse 201 : `data.company_id`, `data.api_key` (une seule fois), `status` sans hash."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 201 or error', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect([201,401,403,409,500]).to.include(pm.response.code);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('JSON has data or error', function () {",
                  "  try { const j = pm.response.json(); pm.expect(j.data !== undefined || j.error !== undefined).to.be.true; } catch (e) { pm.expect.fail('Invalid JSON'); }",
                  "});",
                  "try {",
                  "  const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "  if (j.data && j.data.company_id) {",
                  "    pm.environment.set('enterprise_id', j.data.company_id);",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('enterprise_id', j.data.company_id);",
                  "  }",
                  "  if (j.data && j.data.api_key) {",
                  "    pm.environment.set('api_key', j.data.api_key);",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('api_key', j.data.api_key);",
                  "  }",
                  "} catch (e) {}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
